OL,3,C'Hard and embarrassing to admit':
OL,4,CUnpaid carers struggling to make ends
OL,5,Cmeet
OL,7,F"We're in arrears with the electric, I
OL,8,Fdo make sure that there is food in the
OL,9,Fcupboards. If I eat less then I eat
OL,10,Fless, if it's the way to do it then I
OL,11,Fhave to do it because at the end of
OL,12,Fthe day, my family comes first, not
OL,13,Fme."
OL,15,FHis comments come as new research by
OL,16,FCarer's UK found that more than a
OL,17,Fquarter of the region's unpaid carers
OL,18,Fare living in poverty - meaning they
OL,19,Fare already having cut back on
OL,20,Fessentials like heating and food.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G4/9
